# Setup Guide

This guide will help you get the M365 User Deactivator GUI up and running on your system.

---

## 1. Prerequisites

- **Windows 10/11** (recommended)
- **Python 3.8 or higher**  
  Download from [python.org](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
- **Git** (optional, for cloning the repo)  
  Download from [git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/downloads)
- **Microsoft 365 Admin Access**
- **Azure Active Directory (Entra ID) Admin Access**

---

## 2. Clone or Download the Repository

**Option A: Using Git**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/m365-user-deactivator-gui.git
cd m365-user-deactivator-gui

Option B: Download ZIP

Go to your repository on GitHub.
Click the green "Code" button, then "Download ZIP".
Extract the ZIP file and open the extracted folder.
3. Install Python (if not already installed)
Download and install Python from python.org
During installation, check the box that says "Add Python to PATH"
Check your Python version:

bash
Copy
python --version
# or
py --version
4. Install Dependencies
From inside your project folder, run:

bash
Copy
pip install -r requirements.txt
If pip is not recognized, try:

bash
Copy
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt

or

bash
Copy
py -m pip install -r requirements.txt
5. Azure App Registration (Required for M365 Access)
Go to Azure Portal
Navigate to Azure Active Directory > App registrations
Click New registration
Enter a name (e.g., "M365 Deactivator Tool")
Select Accounts in this organizational directory only
Click Register
After registration:

Copy your Application (client) ID
Copy your Directory (tenant) ID
Create a Client Secret:

In your app registration, go to Certificates & secrets
Click New client secret
Add a description and set an expiration
Click Add and copy the Value immediately
Add API Permissions:

Go to API permissions > Add a permission
Choose Microsoft Graph > Application permissions
Add:
User.ReadWrite.All
Directory.ReadWrite.All
DeviceManagementManagedDevices.ReadWrite.All
UserAuthenticationMethod.ReadWrite.All
Click Grant admin consent for your organization
6. Run the Application
From your project folder, run:

bash
Copy
python m365_user_deactivator_gui.py
or

bash
Copy
py m365_user_deactivator_gui.py
7. First Use
The GUI will open.
Enter your Tenant ID, Client ID, and Client Secret from your Azure App Registration.
Click Connect to M365.
Search for a user by first and last name.
Select the user and start the offboarding process.
8. Troubleshooting
If you encounter issues, see TROUBLESHOOTING.md in this repository.
Common issues include missing dependencies, authentication errors, or permission problems.
9. Updating
To get the latest version, run:

bash
Copy
git pull
from your project folder (if you cloned with Git).

Need more help?
Open an issue on the GitHub repository or consult the troubleshooting guide.


---
